name: IV. Anatomy
description:
Needless to say our bodies adapted to two dimensions very quickly.
To be honest it’s hard for me to imagine returning to the previous state of one-dimension.
I propably should tell you more about our new physiognomy. 
The division we observed (φ) quickly became sacred to us.
It give us life - just like the air you breathe, sustain yours.

We didn’t need any other dimension.

At the very center of our two-dimensional body is an infinite 
Fibonacci spiral.
